                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4205: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-30T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 30, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 30—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>63. Reference is to my telegram No. 62 of June 29, 8 p.m.<note n="64"
                        xml:id="d122fn64">Not printed.</note> In the event that we need Belgian
                    support for further steps, it will be helpful to me, and my hand will be
                    strengthened if the Department can send an acknowledgment of the Belgian reply
                    in the warmest possible terms. The Belgian Cabinet has run some considerable
                    risk in making a favorable reply before the French decision is announced, in
                    spite of French pressure, against the desires of public opinion and the press,
                    and with the realization that they will have a fight to face the moment the text
                    of the reply becomes known. If we can do anything <pb facs="0293" n="179"
                        xml:id="pg_179"/> without engaging ourselves as to details to support them
                    in general terms it will have genuine value as moral support.</p>
                <p>You can judge the sort of message which will have the desired effect. I would not
                    of course suggest any definite assurances to the Belgians.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
